         I bought all my spells one to two full circle before being able to use them pre-50. I have the majority of my 53-60 spells sitting in the bank.</P><P>Why? I pick them up when convienient so that when I'm close to that level and stopping by the bank I can just load them to my inventory and save another trip looking for them or heading back to the bank to get them. My close friends already know which ones I need and keep and eye out for them, as I do for them. If we can get/afford a spell for each other we buy it. We then GIVE that spell to the other. </P><P>Sometimes we get duplicates in which case the duplicate is sold or traded for another spell. Usually given to a guild member first. Hell, there's been alot of times that we just give it away to someone and eat the loss of coin. Remember, this is a game. Loosing 10kpp by enhancing the enjoyment of another person can be its own reward. Granted, doing that too much can lower your own enjoyment some, but every so often is no big deal.</P><P>Necro drop spells I loot and have are usually given away free if I see someone looking for it. I don't know how many research and drop spells I've given away. I'm sure many other necros on this board will say the same. </P><P>So to the original poster...</P><P><font size=6> FUCK YOU </font id=size6> </P><P>You sir, are an ass. Happy hunting.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=264137" target="_blank" target="_blank">Charbonez Soulmark</a><BR>Duzzil Ro<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
